This dashboard helps Job Seekers, Job Transitioners, and Job Swappers find information about the job market, which is often scattered and hard to understand. 
It uses real job postings from 2024 in data science, including job titles, salaries, and locations. The project offers an easy way to explore market trends and salaries.

Skills Showcased
This project highlights essential features of Power BI. Here's what we learned:

- Data Transformation (ETL) with Power Query**: Cleaned and organized the raw data for analysis by fixing blanks, changing data types, and adding new columns.  
- Implicit Measures: Created measures to gain key insights and track important numbers like Median Yearly Salary and Job Count.  
- Core Charts: Used various charts like Column, Bar, Line, and Area Charts to compare job counts and see trends over time.  
- Geospatial Analysis: Used Map Charts to show where jobs are located worldwide.  
- KPI Indicators & Tables: Displayed key metrics using Cards and provided detailed, sortable data through Tables.  
- Dashboard Design: Designed a user-friendly and visually appealing layout, using both common and unique chart types to effectively communicate the data.  
- Interactive Reporting:  
  - Slicers: These allow users to filter the report by Job Title.  
  - Buttons & Bookmarks: These help users navigate the dashboard smoothly.  
  - Drill-Through: This feature enables users to go from a summary to detailed information about a specific job title.

Dashboard Overview 
The report has two pages: A high-level overview and one for detailed analysis.

- Page 1: High-Level Market View  
  This page shows key numbers like total job count, median salaries, and top job titles, giving a quick snapshot of the job market.

- Page 2: Job Title Drill Through
  Users can click to explore details for a specific job title. This includes salary ranges, work-from-home options, top hiring platforms, and a global map showing job locations.

Conclusion  
This project demonstrates how Power BI can turn raw job posting data into a useful tool for analyzing careers. It allows users to filter and explore data to make informed decisions about their career paths.
